{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":449,"text":"My passions"},{"time":1482,"text":"are music, technology and making things."},{"time":5171,"text":"And it's the combination of these things"},{"time":8354,"text":"that has led me to the hobby of sound visualization,"},{"time":11050,"text":"and, on occasion, has led me to play with fire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15128,"text":"This is a Rubens' tube. It's one of many I've made over the years,"},{"time":17505,"text":"and I have one here tonight."},{"time":19251,"text":"It's about an 8-foot-long tube of metal,"},{"time":20776,"text":"it's got a hundred or so holes on top,"},{"time":22111,"text":"on that side is the speaker, and here"},{"time":23864,"text":"is some lab tubing, and it's connected to this tank"},{"time":26040,"text":"of propane."},{"time":29087,"text":"So, let's fire it up and see what it does."},{"time":37887,"text":"So let's play a 550-herz frequency"},{"time":39778,"text":"and watch what happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41342,"text":"(Frequency)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":49825,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":52538,"text":"It's okay to applaud the laws of physics,"},{"time":54526,"text":"but essentially what's happening here"},{"time":55982,"text":"-- (Laughter) --"},{"time":57742,"text":"is the energy from the sound via the air and gas molecules"},{"time":61750,"text":"is influencing the combustion properties of propane,"},{"time":64254,"text":"creating a visible waveform,"},{"time":66158,"text":"and we can see the alternating regions of compression"},{"time":68478,"text":"and rarefaction that we call frequency,"},{"time":70518,"text":"and the height is showing us amplitude."},{"time":72262,"text":"So let's change the frequency of the sound,"},{"time":74590,"text":"and watch what happens to the fire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76015,"text":"(Higher frequency)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86145,"text":"So every time we hit a resonant frequency we get a standing wave"},{"time":89495,"text":"and that emergent sine curve of fire."},{"time":91195,"text":"So let's turn that off. We're indoors."},{"time":92773,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":98364,"text":"I also have with me a flame table."},{"time":100711,"text":"It's very similar to a Rubens' tube, and it's also used"},{"time":102276,"text":"for visualizing the physical properties of sound,"},{"time":104397,"text":"such as eigenmodes, so let's fire it up"},{"time":106365,"text":"and see what it does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112292,"text":"Ooh. (Laughter)"},{"time":116760,"text":"Okay. Now, while the table comes up to pressure,"},{"time":119734,"text":"let me note here that the sound is not traveling"},{"time":121406,"text":"in perfect lines. It's actually traveling in all directions,"},{"time":124152,"text":"and the Rubens' tube's a little like bisecting those waves"},{"time":127261,"text":"with a line, and the flame table's a little like"},{"time":129257,"text":"bisecting those waves with a plane,"},{"time":131111,"text":"and it can show a little more subtle complexity, which is why"},{"time":135111,"text":"I like to use it to watch Geoff Farina play guitar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137464,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":179745,"text":"All right, so it's a delicate dance."},{"time":181510,"text":"If you watch closely â€” (Applause)"},{"time":184055,"text":"If you watch closely, you may have seen"},{"time":186822,"text":"some of the eigenmodes, but also you may have seen"},{"time":189294,"text":"that jazz music is better with fire."},{"time":193911,"text":"Actually, a lot of things are better with fire in my world,"},{"time":195921,"text":"but the fire's just a foundation."},{"time":198353,"text":"It shows very well that eyes can hear,"},{"time":199501,"text":"and this is interesting to me because"},{"time":200896,"text":"technology allows us to present sound to the eyes"},{"time":203750,"text":"in ways that accentuate the strength of the eyes"},{"time":206613,"text":"for seeing sound, such as the removal of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209310,"text":"So here, I'm using a rendering algorithm to paint"},{"time":212694,"text":"the frequencies of the song \"Smells Like Teen Spirit\""},{"time":215157,"text":"in a way that the eyes can take them in"},{"time":217197,"text":"as a single visual impression, and the technique"},{"time":219441,"text":"will also show the strengths of the visual cortex"},{"time":221414,"text":"for pattern recognition."},{"time":223030,"text":"So if I show you another song off this album,"},{"time":224909,"text":"and another, your eyes will easily pick out"},{"time":228390,"text":"the use of repetition by the band Nirvana,"},{"time":231318,"text":"and in the frequency distribution, the colors,"},{"time":233175,"text":"you can see the clean-dirty-clean sound"},{"time":236223,"text":"that they are famous for,"},{"time":237430,"text":"and here is the entire album as a single visual impression,"},{"time":241430,"text":"and I think this impression is pretty powerful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243310,"text":"At least, it's powerful enough that"},{"time":245024,"text":"if I show you these four songs,"},{"time":246366,"text":"and I remind you that this is \"Smells Like Teen Spirit,\""},{"time":248807,"text":"you can probably correctly guess, without listening"},{"time":251126,"text":"to any music at all, that the song"},{"time":252560,"text":"a die hard Nirvana fan would enjoy is this song,"},{"time":254854,"text":"\"I'll Stick Around\" by the Foo Fighters,"},{"time":257110,"text":"whose lead singer is Dave Grohl,"},{"time":259110,"text":"who was the drummer in Nirvana."},{"time":262888,"text":"The songs are a little similar, but mostly"},{"time":264188,"text":"I'm just interested in the idea that someday maybe"},{"time":265814,"text":"we'll buy a song because we like the way it looks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270226,"text":"All right, now for some more sound data."},{"time":271326,"text":"This is data from a skate park,"},{"time":273978,"text":"and this is Mabel Davis skate park"},{"time":276010,"text":"in Austin, Texas. (Skateboard sounds)"},{"time":278152,"text":"And the sounds you're hearing came from eight"},{"time":279526,"text":"microphones attached to obstacles around the park,"},{"time":281742,"text":"and it sounds like chaos, but actually"},{"time":283926,"text":"all the tricks start with a very distinct slap,"},{"time":287273,"text":"but successful tricks end with a pop,"},{"time":288877,"text":"whereas unsuccessful tricks"},{"time":290670,"text":"more of a scratch and a tumble,"},{"time":292526,"text":"and tricks on the rail will ring out like a gong, and"},{"time":296536,"text":"voices occupy very unique frequencies in the skate park."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299326,"text":"So if we were to render these sounds visually,"},{"time":301264,"text":"we might end up with something like this."},{"time":302671,"text":"This is all 40 minutes of the recording,"},{"time":305127,"text":"and right away the algorithm tells us"},{"time":307287,"text":"a lot more tricks are missed than are made,"},{"time":309360,"text":"and also a trick on the rails is a lot more likely"},{"time":311695,"text":"to produce a cheer, and if you look really closely,"},{"time":314567,"text":"we can tease out traffic patterns."},{"time":316300,"text":"You see the skaters often trick in this direction. The obstacles are easier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322387,"text":"And in the middle of the recording, the mics pick this up,"},{"time":324092,"text":"but later in the recording, this kid shows up,"},{"time":326896,"text":"and he starts using a line at the top of the park"},{"time":329824,"text":"to do some very advanced tricks on something"},{"time":331626,"text":"called the tall rail."},{"time":332729,"text":"And it's fascinating. At this moment in time,"},{"time":334601,"text":"all the rest of the skaters turn their lines 90 degrees"},{"time":338104,"text":"to stay out of his way."},{"time":339882,"text":"You see, there's a subtle etiquette in the skate park,"},{"time":342425,"text":"and it's led by key influencers,"},{"time":344025,"text":"and they tend to be the kids who can do the best tricks,"},{"time":347273,"text":"or wear red pants, and on this day the mics picked that up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349703,"text":"All right, from skate physics to theoretical physics."},{"time":353604,"text":"I'm a big fan of Stephen Hawking,"},{"time":355220,"text":"and I wanted to use all eight hours"},{"time":356556,"text":"of his Cambridge lecture series to create an homage."},{"time":359143,"text":"Now, in this series he's speaking with the aid of a computer,"},{"time":362207,"text":"which actually makes identifying the ends of sentences"},{"time":365311,"text":"fairly easy. So I wrote a steering algorithm."},{"time":368737,"text":"It listens to the lecture, and then it uses"},{"time":370697,"text":"the amplitude of each word to move a point on the x-axis,"},{"time":373384,"text":"and it uses the inflection of sentences"},{"time":376017,"text":"to move a same point up and down on the y-axis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378171,"text":"And these trend lines, you can see, there's more questions"},{"time":380945,"text":"than answers in the laws of physics,"},{"time":382815,"text":"and when we reach the end of a sentence,"},{"time":384848,"text":"we place a star at that location."},{"time":387183,"text":"So there's a lot of sentences, so a lot of stars,"},{"time":389983,"text":"and after rendering all of the audio, this is what we get."},{"time":392339,"text":"This is Stephen Hawking's universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395268,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":402205,"text":"It's all eight hours of the Cambridge lecture series"},{"time":404692,"text":"taken in as a single visual impression,"},{"time":406540,"text":"and I really like this image,"},{"time":408297,"text":"but a lot of people think it's fake."},{"time":410105,"text":"So I made a more interactive version,"},{"time":412449,"text":"and the way I did that is I used their position in time"},{"time":417905,"text":"in the lecture to place these stars into 3D space,"},{"time":420272,"text":"and with some custom software and a Kinect,"},{"time":422673,"text":"I can walk right into the lecture."},{"time":425336,"text":"I'm going to wave through the Kinect here"},{"time":427136,"text":"and take control, and now I'm going to reach out"},{"time":428968,"text":"and I'm going to touch a star, and when I do,"},{"time":432207,"text":"it will play the sentence"},{"time":434151,"text":"that generated that star."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435616,"text":"Stephen Hawking: There is one, and only one, arrangement"},{"time":439432,"text":"in which the pieces make a complete picture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442231,"text":"Jared Ficklin: Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":446379,"text":"There are 1,400 stars."},{"time":449552,"text":"It's a really fun way to explore the lecture,"},{"time":451216,"text":"and, I hope, a fitting homage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452683,"text":"All right. Let me close with a work in progress."},{"time":458155,"text":"I think, after 30 years, the opportunity exists"},{"time":461138,"text":"to create an enhanced version of closed captioning."},{"time":463242,"text":"Now, we've all seen a lot of TEDTalks online,"},{"time":465361,"text":"so let's watch one now with the sound turned off"},{"time":468288,"text":"and the closed captioning turned on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472210,"text":"There's no closed captioning for the TED theme song,"},{"time":474356,"text":"and we're missing it, but if you've watched enough of these,"},{"time":476469,"text":"you hear it in your mind's ear,"},{"time":477838,"text":"and then applause starts."},{"time":480821,"text":"It usually begins here, and it grows and then it falls."},{"time":483011,"text":"Sometimes you get a little star applause,"},{"time":484988,"text":"and then I think even Bill Gates takes a nervous breath,"},{"time":487474,"text":"and the talk begins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489164,"text":"All right, so let's watch this clip again."},{"time":494862,"text":"This time, I'm not going to talk at all."},{"time":496118,"text":"There's still going to be no audio,"},{"time":497485,"text":"but what I am going to do is I'm going to render the sound"},{"time":499389,"text":"visually in real time at the bottom of the screen."},{"time":503705,"text":"So watch closely and see what your eyes can hear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527880,"text":"This is fairly amazing to me."},{"time":529760,"text":"Even on the first view, your eyes will successfully"},{"time":533093,"text":"pick out patterns, but on repeated views,"},{"time":536181,"text":"your brain actually gets better"},{"time":537870,"text":"at turning these patterns into information."},{"time":539526,"text":"You can get the tone and the timbre"},{"time":541117,"text":"and the pace of the speech,"},{"time":542340,"text":"things that you can't get out of closed captioning."},{"time":544404,"text":"That famous scene in horror movies"},{"time":546588,"text":"where someone is walking up from behind"},{"time":549236,"text":"is something you can see,"},{"time":551196,"text":"and I believe this information would be something"},{"time":553900,"text":"that is useful at times when the audio is turned off"},{"time":556703,"text":"or not heard at all, and I speculate that deaf audiences"},{"time":559644,"text":"might actually even be better"},{"time":560821,"text":"at seeing sound than hearing audiences."},{"time":562602,"text":"I don't know. It's a theory right now."},{"time":564100,"text":"Actually, it's all just an idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565621,"text":"And let me end by saying that sound moves in all directions,"},{"time":569812,"text":"and so do ideas."},{"time":571789,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}